11/01/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- OSCE Chairman-in-Office Slovenian Foreign Minister Dimitrij Rupel, visited Kosovo on Tuesday (11 January) for meetings with UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen and local officials. Issues related to the political and security situation, as well as the decentralisation process in the province, will dominate the agenda. 
On Monday, Jessen-Petersen said that division is not the solution to Kosovo's problems. His comment followed a meeting with Kosovo President Ibrahim Rugova, Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj and Parliament Speaker Nexhat Daci. In Belgrade, meanwhile, Serbian President Boris Tadic met with a Kosovo Serb delegation. (Danas - 11/01/05; OSCE Web site, Tanjug, Beta, KosovaLive - 10/01/05)
